# Electronics Circuit Simulator

A browser-based circuit simulator where users can build and test basic electrical circuits using resistors, LEDs, and wires. The app lets you place components, connect them, and instantly see how changes in the circuit affect voltage, current, and LED behavior.

## Live Demo

Client: https://ominous-fiesta-69j4xqrq49r72r456-5173.app.github.dev/

## Features

- Place components on a grid-based workspace
- Drag and move components freely
- Connect components using wires
- Resistors with adjustable resistance values
- LEDs that react to circuit conditions
- Real-time voltage and current calculation
- Series and parallel circuit behavior
- Snap-to-grid positioning
- Delete mode for removing components and wires
- Animated current flow visualization

## Tech Stack

- React
- TypeScript
- Vite
- Node.js (Express backend for development)
- CSS / Inline styling

## How to Run Locally

### Install dependencies
```bash
npm install
Start the client
cd project/client
npm run dev
Open in browser
http://localhost:5173
Project Structure
project/
  client/
    src/
      App.tsx
      pages/
        Lab.tsx
  server/
    index.ts
How It Works
Components are placed on a grid-based canvas
Users connect components using draggable wires
Circuit behavior updates in real time
Resistance affects current flow using basic circuit rules
LEDs turn on or off based on voltage conditions
Users can switch between wire mode and delete mode


           
